(3136, 1, '2017-09-20 16:45:07', '2017-09-20 16:45:07', '[vc_row thb_full_width="true" css=".vc_custom_1505925470011{padding-top: 240px !important;padding-bottom: 240px !important;background-image: url(http://cloud1.gauravpanwar.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/Macarons-online-bestellen-Den-Haag-Chocolade-Franse-Macarons-Dark-Chocolate-Valrhona-Bank.jpg?id=3161) !important;}" type="full_width_background" parallax_speed="1" el_class="aboutus_header"][vc_column][vc_column_text]\n<h6 style="text-align: center;">IT ALL STARTED WITH</h6>\n<h2 style="text-align: center;">CHOCOLATE</h2>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1411505471768{border-width: 0px 0px 1px !important;padding-top: 80px !important;padding-bottom: 80px !important;}" type="full_width_background" parallax_speed="1"][vc_column animation="animation scale"][vc_column_text]\n<h1 style="text-align: center; font-weight: 300; font-size: 60px; line-height: 66px;">Food, especially cakes and pastries, should always be\n<strong style="font-weight: 500;">DELICIOUS</strong> and <strong style="font-weight: 500;">HEALTHY!</strong>.</h1>\n[/vc_column_text][thb_gap height="30"][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/4"][thb_iconbox icon="" heading="Delicious foods" animation="animation fade-in" image="3138"]<b>Wholesome &amp; fresh ingredients</b> only food, no weird add-ons[/thb_iconbox][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/4"][thb_iconbox icon="" heading="Healthy foods" animation="animation fade-in" image="3140"]<b>Organic</b> ingredients as much as possible Flour, eggs, creams etc.. Are all organic[/thb_iconbox][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/4"][thb_iconbox icon="" heading="Only THE BEST CHOCOLATE" animation="animation fade-in" image="3143"]<b>Valrhona </b>Chocolate\nNever compromise on that major ingredient\nused by all star chefs and pastry chefs[/thb_iconbox][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/4"][thb_iconbox icon="" heading="HOME MADE, Truly, 100%" animation="animation fade-in" image="3141"]One Day I\'ll be a grand\'ma and I will qualify for the memories of my kids\' children as "my grand\'ma makes the best cakes" [/thb_iconbox][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row column_padding="false" row_padding="true" thb_full_width="true" type="full_width_content" parallax_speed="1" css=".vc_custom_1466617452163{border-top-width: 1px !important;padding-top: 40px !important;border-top-color: #ececec !important;border-top-style: solid !important;}" el_class="text-center"][vc_column][vc_column_text]\n\n[small_title title="WHO WE ARE"]\n\n[/vc_column_text][thb_gap height="40"][thb_slider navigation="true" bullets="true" images="3149,3150,3151,3152,3153,3154" height="400" width="1920"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1411505599293{border-width: 0px 0px 1px !important;padding-top: 80px !important;padding-bottom: 80px !important;}" type="in_container" parallax_speed="1"][vc_column][vc_column_text]<strong>Cook to Celebrate!</strong>\nCooking is the celebration of togetherness, sharing and creativity.\nDaria\'s vision is about sharing elegant and delicious creations with amateurs of intense, refined or delicate tastes, enthusiasts of wholesome ingredients and activists of slow food.\n\nGood food is made in small quantities, with all the passion and respect it deserves.\n\nGood food is meant to bring people together, stimulate memories of other great table moments and generate common memories for the future. Whenever someone will be heard quoting during a lunch, a diner or a tasting "Oh, and do you remember this cake we had from Daria, how incredibly tasty and intense it was?!" This is when the mission will be accomplished.\n\nEmotional memories stay with us for decades and Cook to Celebrate want to be part of them and, even better, to be a source of them!\n\nCook To Celebrate operates out of Daria\'s own kitchen in Den Haag. Her passion runs back to her childhood in Poland, enjoying the traditional cakes and cuisine of her mum and has been enriched with a good dose of French pastry making influence when she found out that the best cooking chocolate in the world, the one every three Michelin star chef mentions in their book, Valrhona, originates from a mere 20 km from her husband\'s native village. There couldn\'t have been better coincidence.\n\nOver the past few years, Daria has been on various pastry professional courses, with Lenotre in Paris and Versailles, with Valrhona in Tain l\'Hermitage and has been experimenting with recipes and ingredients at every opportunity, to the sheer enjoyment of her husband and children!\n\n&nbsp;\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a style="text-align: center;" href="http://cloud1.gauravpanwar.com/contact-us/">Contact Us</a></p>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'About Us', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '156-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-09-20 16:45:07', '2017-09-20 16:45:07', '', 156, 'http://cloud1.gauravpanwar.com/156-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
